{"tid":1894224,"cid":33,"subCid":0,"title":"文章分享：民主會自動到來嗎？英國的經驗","createTime":"2020-02-23T18:44:53.000Z","updateTime":"2020-02-23T18:46:34.000Z","uid":276028,"like":0,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":2,"replies":[{"pid":"78f806cadde580458093aa0d86ae27852981a714","tid":1894224,"uid":276028,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-02-23T18:44:53.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"https://www.boyangu.com/2011/03/deomcracy_uk/\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.boyangu.com%2F2011%2F03%2Fdeomcracy_uk%2F&d=SulGM1C%2FSMvfI9hDp2hpAv8K46P7%2BXxs1F7ZCKkfkQw%3D&h=6411bd8d\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.boyangu.com/2011/03/deomcracy_uk/</a><br />\n歷史上不存在先經濟，後民主的發展。當然歷史上所有老牌民主國家，民主並非一蹴而就，而是經過該國人民不停的抗爭才能完成，甚至要幾代人的努力；但是這些國家都沒有所謂「先經濟，後民主」的發展模式，它們都是在發展經濟期間，政治制度逐步改善。"},{"pid":"a84f7cc0f500b993f72a97bfaefba6ebf1913c30","tid":1894224,"uid":258566,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-02-23T18:46:34.000Z","msg":"此回覆已被刪除"}]}